The paper discusses the use of bitmap indexes to speed up advanced queries in databases, which is a topic closely related to data management and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves algorithmic design issues, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper mentions set operations and Boolean queries, which are relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
